                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c00">Additionally, so much of the internet is ephemeral, compared to the content that students or researchers would have been photocopying when Umberto Eco wrote the piece that&#x27;s quoted in the article. For this reason, if I find an interesting article&#x2F;page&#x2F;whatever, I tend to save a local copy even if I don&#x27;t know when or if I&#x27;ll read it. It might not be online anymore when it turns out to be useful.<span>
